@NODE "intro" "ZoomIT 1.0 - Introduction"
@PREV "main"
@NEXT "req"

 @{b}@{u}Introduction@{uu}@{ub}

 Why another magnify/zoom tool ?

 The idea of this tool was created as an applet for the upcomming tray.library by
 Adam 'ChaoZer' Waldenberg. I know that that MorphOS comes with a zoom-tool (by Michal Rybinski)
 allready, but I though I could make an version which had some more options.
 And that's when I thought... why not create a stand-alone application of my tray-applet.

 And that's how ZoomIT was born =)

@ENDNODE

@NODE "req" "ZoomIT 1.0 - Requirements"
@PREV "intro"
@NEXT "install"

 @{b}@{u}Requirements@{uu}@{ub}

 This program needs following stuff:

 · MorphOS 1.x, AmigaOS 3.x or AROS (x86)
 · CyberGraphX or P96 (CGX-emulation API).
 · Magic User Interface (MUI).

@ENDNODE

@NODE "install" "ZoomIT 1.0 - Installation"
@PREV "req"
@NEXT "usage"

 @{b}@{u}Installation@{uu}@{ub}

 This program doesn't need any installation and because of that doesn't come with
 any form of installer script. Just place it where you want and run it from there! =)
 
@ENDNODE

@NODE "usage" "ZoomIT 1.0 - Usage"
@PREV "install"
@NEXT "faq"

 @{b}@{u}Usage@{uu}@{ub}

 This program consist of a window which displays graphics from the mouse-position.
 The shown graphic is either a plain copy of a area or X times zoomed/magnified data.

 Most of the functions is placed in the menu of this application, but if you have a
 wheel-button on the mouse the zoom-factor can be changed by moving it.
 The magnify percentage is shown in the top-border of the window.


 @{b}Menu - Project :@{ub}

   Here is the normal (dull) menu options which let us see the about-window, iconify
   or quit the program. Really not much to say about it, it's much self explaining (I hope) =)


 @{b}Menu - Settings :@{ub}

   This is where the 'Magic' is changed.

   @{b}Magnification@{ub}
   In this menu you can change the magnify percentage and refresh rate of the mouse trail.
   The program can have a magnify percentage between 100% - 1200% which is always shown in the
   top border of the window.

   @{b}Refresh Rate@{ub}
   The refresh rate is the option where you set how 'quick' the update of the graphics should be
   re-written. Under this menu option there is also a Frozen-option which let you hold the last
   mouse coordinates for the zoom-position. By enabling this option the word 'Frozen' is written
   at the top border of the window. You can change the magnify percentage even if this option
   is enabled.

   @{b}Scale Mode@{ub}
   In this menu you can also change scale mode, where CyberGraphX is the default option (fastest), but
   since some system does not work correctly (AROS and old P96-systems) you can use the -internal- mode
   which is built-in software scale method.
   The internal mode is much slower and requires more memory than the CyberGraphX mode.
   @{i}This menu option is not part of MorphOS or AROS-version.@{ui}


   @{b}Color Mode@{ub}
   This menu let you select what color component that shall be included in the output-window.
   And as a extra effect, you can choose to se the magnified graphics as greyscale output and
   or in a inverted way.

   @{b}Miscellaneous@{ub}
   Here you can choose incase you want to make the Quit-button to iconify the program rather than close it.
   You can also select borderless window to remove the border from ZoomITs window (might not work on AROS).


   Under the settings menu there is also standard MUI-functions such as Snapshot/UnSnapshot
   and MUI Settings.


 @{b}ARexx :@{ub}

   ZoomIT has a small set of ARexx-commands built-in, which can change the function of the
   program by scripts or a single lite of rexx-command.

    @{b}MAGNIFY <arg>@{ub}
    This is command to change the mangnify percentage (valid input-values = 1 -> 12)

    @{b}REFRESH <arg>@{ub}
    This command change the refresh-rate on the graphics update in the window (valid input-values = 1, 5, 15, 30 or 60)

    Apart from these commands above, the normal MUI-command works aswell.
    QUIT, HIDE, SHOW etc...


    To test the ARexx-interface, start ZoomIT and open up a shell-window.
    at the prompt write :

    rx "OPTIONS RESULTS; ADDRESS ZOOMIT.1; 'MAGNIFY 4'"

    This command line will change the zoom factor to 4 (ie. 400%)




 That's really all =)
 Didn't I tell you this was a pretty simple tool ? ;)

@ENDNODE

@NODE "faq" "ZoomIT 1.0 - FAQ"
@PREV "usageprefs"
@NEXT "news"

@{b}@{u}FAQ - Frequently Asked Question@{uu}@{ub}

* @{b}Q = Question@{ub}
* @{b}A = Answer@{ub}

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q - Why do ZoomIT refuse to start on my MorphOS-system ?

A - ZoomIT uses the new AboutBox-mcc on MorphOS-systems, if you have 2.x
    it's allready there. If you still using 1.4 please use the latest update
    pack if you havn't allready and you'll be able to use WiiLoader again =)

    http://www.morphos-team.net/downloads.html

==============================================================================

Q - The graphics is updated even if I use the "Frozen" option, how come ?

A - The Frozen-option don't stop the graphics to not be updated,
    it only freezes the current mouse-position and freezes the "zoom glass"
    to that position until the option is disabled.

==============================================================================

Q - I'm using Picasso 96 and the magnified graphics looks like sh*t ?

A - This application is created using the RTG-software that set the
    real standard for gfx-cards on the Amiga, namely CyberGraphX.
    By using a system that clones the functionality of this RTG-system
    I cannot say to 100% that it will work as intended.

    Older versions of P96 and AROS CyberGraphX-emulation is not entirely
    working correctly with the ScalePixelArray()-function.
    So for a solution on this please try check the meny option
    "-Internal-" in scale method and hopefully it will work better.

==============================================================================

Q - Why is the -Internal- scale mechanism so slow compared using CyberGraphX ?

A - It shuffles around a lot more data than normal operation,
    this was mainly added due limitation in AROS-CyberGraphX emulation.
    Use only this option incase the normal option does not work for you.

==============================================================================

Q - I cannot get the ARexx-commands to work ?

A - Check first if you have RexxMast presented and running in the system,
    if not enable it and try again.

Q - I do have it enabled, but it still do not work, why ?

A - Do you have multiple instances of ZoomIT running at the same time ?
    Be sure to pass the command to right one of the programs.
    Note that there is .1 .2 etc. in the command adress and if you point at
    wrong instance the desired window might not be affected.

Q - Nope, it still does not work ?

A - Are you using AROS ?
    I have not got this to work in my vmwaros-setup myself, there might
    be so that the ARexx-implementation is not completely working in AROS
    yet, but when it is implemented it should work IMHO.
------------------------------------------------------------------------------ 


@ENDNODE

@NODE "news" "ZoomIT 1.0 - What's new?"
@PREV "usage"
@NEXT "history"

 @{b}@{u}What's new@{uu}@{ub}

 · Now possible to use the application without window borders.
 · Cleaned up the menu layout (removed redundant stuff, use MUI-settings instead)
 · Removed space and frame in the window (only scaled data is now shown)
 · Updated the program to make use of MorphOS 2.0-features
 · Internal optimizations (thanks to Christian Rosentreter)
 · Plus lot more changes!


@ENDNODE

@NODE "history" "ZoomIT 1.0 - History"
@PREV "news"
@NEXT "future"

 @{b}@{u}History@{uu}@{ub}

 · 26-Feb-2009 - Fourth release (v1.0)

   - Now possible to use the application without window borders.
   - Cleaned up the menu layout (removed redundant stuff, use MUI-settings instead)
   - Removed space and frame in the window (only scaled data is now shown)
   - Updated the program to make use of MorphOS 2.0-features
   - Internal optimizations (thanks to Christian Rosentreter)
   - Plus lot more changes!


 · 24-Jun-2008 - Third release (v0.3)

   - AmigaOS4 native version (Thanks to Daniel Westerberg)
   - Wheel mouse support when window is active (on AmigaOS,  MorphOS-version allready had this option)
   - ARexx-support
   - New settings options like start the program iconified and quit-button = iconify.
   - Option to select which color components to be included in the resulting output.
   - Option for grey scale output.
   - Option for inverted graphics.
   - Smaller optimizations


 · 02-Jun-2008 - Second release (v0.2)

   - AROS support
   - Added a new internal scale method for system that cannot properly handle ScalePixelArray()-calls
     this means that you can use it on UAE (using P96-driver) and AROS without the scaling looks like cr@p =)

   - MorphOS version unchanged (worked as intended since previous release) =)


 · 21-Feb-2006 - First official release of ZoomIT (v0.1)
   

@ENDNODE

